Key results:

local stiffness field

    m(r) ∝ g_b(r)^0.296

preferred cumulative map

    S(r) = ∫₀ʳ m(s) ds

corrected master-curve exponents

    power-law stiffness         ν = 0.940
    density-coupled stiffness   ν = 0.947
    exponential-core stiffness  ν = 0.950

These results show that the stretched-exponential master curve can be
understood as exponential saturation in cumulative stiffness rather
than an independent fitting ansatz.


